WEBVTT

00:00:01.419 --> 00:00:06.259
The day was nice in 1133 CE.

00:00:06.259 --> 00:00:12.859
Jesus was busy in the temple teaching just a few days prior to his death.

00:00:12.859 --> 00:00:19.780
He silenced the scribes and the Pharisees with his irrefutable logic, at the same time

00:00:19.780 --> 00:00:25.620
sharing some of the most profound teachings of his earthly ministry.

00:00:25.620 --> 00:00:32.899
For instance, pay back Caesar's things to Caesar, but God's things to God.

00:00:32.899 --> 00:00:42.380
Then one of the scribes came forward and asked Jesus, what is the greatest commandment?

00:00:42.380 --> 00:00:44.780
How did Jesus respond?

00:00:44.780 --> 00:00:51.380
His response would have far-reaching implications even down to our day for anyone claiming

00:00:51.380 --> 00:00:53.259
to be a Christian.

00:00:53.259 --> 00:00:58.380
We find his response in Mark chapter 12, I invite you to turn there.

00:00:58.380 --> 00:01:02.939
Mark chapter 12, and notice please with me verses 29 and 30.

00:01:02.939 --> 00:01:11.540
Mark 12, 29 and 30, Jesus answered the first or the most important commandment.

00:01:11.540 --> 00:01:18.579
The greatest commandment is, here, O Israel, Jehovah, our God is one Jehovah.

00:01:18.579 --> 00:01:26.659
And you must love Jehovah your God with your whole heart and with your whole soul and

00:01:26.659 --> 00:01:31.579
with your whole mind and with your whole strength.

00:01:31.579 --> 00:01:36.060
You must love Jehovah, love God.

00:01:36.060 --> 00:01:38.299
It sounds simple, right?

00:01:38.299 --> 00:01:44.500
Well billions of people claim to love God, but they love pleasures more, or they're

00:01:44.500 --> 00:01:51.540
willing to fight and kill their fellow man, or they refuse to live by God's moral standards.

00:01:51.540 --> 00:01:56.219
All such things contradict their claim to love God.

00:01:56.219 --> 00:02:02.140
Well Jesus demonstrated that love of God requires more than a feeling of affection.

00:02:02.140 --> 00:02:07.060
Jesus stressed how completely we must love God with our whole heart, with our whole soul,

00:02:07.060 --> 00:02:09.780
with our whole mind, with our whole strength.

00:02:09.780 --> 00:02:12.500
Does that leave anything out?

00:02:12.500 --> 00:02:17.620
Our eyes, our ears, our hands?

00:02:17.620 --> 00:02:22.780
Well the study notes on verse 30 help us to understand that this includes our emotions,

00:02:22.780 --> 00:02:25.020
desires, and feelings.

00:02:25.020 --> 00:02:28.620
It includes our intellectual faculties and power of reason.

00:02:28.620 --> 00:02:30.699
It includes our physical and mental strength.

00:02:30.699 --> 00:02:36.500
Yes, our whole being, all that we are, we must devote to our love to Jehovah.

00:02:36.500 --> 00:02:40.099
Love for God must govern a person's entire life.

00:02:40.099 --> 00:02:41.939
Nothing is left out.

00:02:41.939 --> 00:02:48.300
Well, shortly after emphasizing the greatest commandment, and again we're thinking of Jesus,

00:02:48.300 --> 00:02:53.780
he's there in the temple shortly after emphasizing the greatest commandment, Jesus shines a light

00:02:53.780 --> 00:03:01.210
on both bad and good examples of love for God.

00:03:01.210 --> 00:03:05.849
First he sharply condemned the scribes and the Pharisees for their pretense of love for

00:03:05.849 --> 00:03:06.849
God.

00:03:06.849 --> 00:03:13.030
Now, if you want the full condemnation, it's found in Matthew chapter 23.

00:03:13.030 --> 00:03:20.110
Those hypocrites, they gave even the tenth or a tithe of small tiny herbs, but they ignored

00:03:20.110 --> 00:03:25.729
the weightier matters of justice and mercy and faithfulness.

00:03:25.729 --> 00:03:27.090
That was the bad example.

00:03:27.090 --> 00:03:33.090
But then Jesus gave his attention to an outstanding example of love for God.

00:03:33.090 --> 00:03:40.460
If you're still there in Mark chapter 12, notice starting in verse 41.

00:03:40.460 --> 00:03:45.819
And Jesus sat down with the treasury chests in view and began observing how the crowd

00:03:45.819 --> 00:03:49.139
was dropping money into the treasury chests.

00:03:49.139 --> 00:03:52.860
And many rich people were dropping in many coins.

00:03:52.860 --> 00:03:58.780
Now a poor widow came and dropped in two small coins, a very little value.

00:03:58.780 --> 00:04:03.740
So he called his disciples to him and said to them, truly, I say to you that this poor

00:04:03.740 --> 00:04:09.139
widow put in more than all the others who put money into the treasury chests.

00:04:09.180 --> 00:04:15.180
So they all put in out of their surplus, but she, out of her want, put in everything she

00:04:15.180 --> 00:04:19.560
had, all she had to live on.

00:04:19.560 --> 00:04:25.399
The coins of the needy widow were worth about 15 minutes wages.

00:04:25.399 --> 00:04:28.120
Yet Jesus expressed his father's view of her worship.

00:04:28.120 --> 00:04:32.240
He commended her whole soul's sacrifice.

00:04:32.240 --> 00:04:34.240
What do we learn?

00:04:34.240 --> 00:04:39.600
Well, clearly the lessons go far beyond material giving.

00:04:39.600 --> 00:04:43.800
Life in our worship of Jehovah is important to him.

00:04:43.800 --> 00:04:50.120
Jehovah doesn't compare us with others or even previous versions of ourselves, younger

00:04:50.120 --> 00:04:52.920
versions of ourselves.

00:04:52.920 --> 00:04:58.879
Jehovah simply wants love for him with our whole heart, soul, mind, and strength.

00:04:58.879 --> 00:05:06.040
Not as they were 10 or 20 years ago, but as they currently are now.

00:05:06.040 --> 00:05:09.600
Now a question in reference to love for Jehovah.

00:05:09.600 --> 00:05:15.800
Is it reasonable for Jehovah to expect us to love him with our whole heart, soul,

00:05:15.800 --> 00:05:17.519
mind, and strength?

00:05:17.519 --> 00:05:19.600
Is it reasonable?

00:05:19.600 --> 00:05:22.399
Yes, absolutely.

00:05:22.399 --> 00:05:24.800
Why can we say that?

00:05:24.800 --> 00:05:32.160
Because Jehovah loves us with his whole heart, soul, mind, and strength.

00:05:32.160 --> 00:05:33.160
How so?

00:05:33.160 --> 00:05:38.720
Well, let's turn to Isaiah chapters 40 through 44.

00:05:38.720 --> 00:05:43.879
And there will consider a few of the many reasons we have to love Jehovah.

00:05:43.879 --> 00:05:49.720
And at the same time, we'll consider some examples of the depth of Jehovah's love for us.

00:05:49.720 --> 00:05:57.459
So our first example is in Isaiah chapter 40 and notice, please verse 11, Isaiah 40 verse

00:05:57.459 --> 00:05:58.459
11.

00:05:58.459 --> 00:06:04.100
There it says, like a shepherd, he will care for his flock.

00:06:04.100 --> 00:06:07.819
With his arm, he will gather together the lambs and in his bosom, he will carry them.

00:06:07.819 --> 00:06:11.019
He will gently lead those nursing their young.

00:06:11.019 --> 00:06:13.420
Here we find a beautiful word picture of Jehovah.

00:06:13.420 --> 00:06:18.100
Jehovah is a tender shepherd.

00:06:18.100 --> 00:06:25.180
At Ezekiel chapter 34 verses 15 and 16, Jehovah says, I myself will feed my sheep.

00:06:25.180 --> 00:06:29.300
The last one I will search for, the stray, I will bring back the injured, I will bandage

00:06:29.300 --> 00:06:35.379
as we notice in the illustration and the weak, I will strengthen what a touching picture

00:06:35.379 --> 00:06:39.819
of compassion and tender care.

00:06:39.819 --> 00:06:46.379
If we fall and hurt ourselves, or if we stumble in the briar patch, sort of speak, Jehovah

00:06:46.379 --> 00:06:48.579
bandages us.

00:06:48.579 --> 00:06:50.740
He helps us to heal.

00:06:50.740 --> 00:06:53.339
When we seek his help, he doesn't reproach us.

00:06:53.339 --> 00:06:56.980
You should have known better, no.

00:06:56.980 --> 00:07:01.779
But he does try to help us not to stray in the future with reminders from his word.

00:07:01.779 --> 00:07:03.579
And what is the effect on the sheep?

00:07:03.579 --> 00:07:07.420
So as we saw in the illustration, he feels secure in Jehovah's care.

00:07:07.420 --> 00:07:09.220
How do we feel in Jehovah's care?

00:07:09.220 --> 00:07:11.819
His compassion at care.

00:07:11.819 --> 00:07:13.060
We too feel secure.

00:07:13.060 --> 00:07:20.939
We might say that Jehovah loves us with all his heart, his compassion.

00:07:20.939 --> 00:07:25.540
Doesn't that increase your love for him?

00:07:25.540 --> 00:07:28.939
Let's consider a second reason why we have that we have to love Jehovah.

00:07:28.939 --> 00:07:34.620
Isaiah chapter 40, notice verses 28 and 29.

00:07:34.620 --> 00:07:36.980
Verse 28 says, Do you not know?

00:07:36.980 --> 00:07:38.899
Have you not heard?

00:07:38.899 --> 00:07:43.939
Jehovah, the creator of the ends of the earth, is a God for all eternity.

00:07:43.939 --> 00:07:47.420
He never tires out or grows weary.

00:07:47.420 --> 00:07:49.300
His understanding is unsearchable.

00:07:49.300 --> 00:07:57.420
He gives power to the tired one and full might to those lacking strength.

00:07:57.420 --> 00:08:09.129
With Jehovah's mighty Holy Spirit, he created everything beginning with his first born son

00:08:09.129 --> 00:08:15.649
to myriads of mighty spirit creatures, to the vast universe with its trillions upon trillions

00:08:15.649 --> 00:08:21.170
of stars, to this beautiful earth with its endless variety of plant and animal life,

00:08:21.170 --> 00:08:26.730
to the human body with its awe-inspiring ability and versatility.

00:08:26.730 --> 00:08:32.220
Jehovah is truly the almighty creator.

00:08:32.220 --> 00:08:34.860
Now think about this.

00:08:34.860 --> 00:08:41.019
What happens when you or I become completely exhausted, completely tired, maybe at the end

00:08:41.019 --> 00:08:43.940
of a long day, when a human becomes physically tired?

00:08:43.940 --> 00:08:45.500
How does he recharge?

00:08:45.500 --> 00:08:50.139
Do we plug into a charging station like an electric car?

00:08:50.139 --> 00:08:51.940
No.

00:08:51.940 --> 00:08:57.580
We're marvelously designed to recharge through rest and the food that we take into our

00:08:57.580 --> 00:08:58.940
bodies are fuel.

00:08:58.940 --> 00:09:01.980
The calories, the energy and food are evidence of Jehovah's love.

00:09:01.980 --> 00:09:08.419
Not only does it recharge us, but it brings us delight, too.

00:09:08.419 --> 00:09:11.220
What did you have for breakfast?

00:09:11.220 --> 00:09:12.980
Maybe here at the assembly hall.

00:09:12.980 --> 00:09:19.539
